{
  "texts": [
    "Output:A few issues with output, such as ambiguity and a diversity of entity kinds, are stated below taking into account the output barriers that have been assessed below [114].",
    "(i) Diverse Entity Types: Indian Languages have unique entity types, such as Caste names, religious entities or traditional names which may not present in standard NER tag sets.",
    "(ii) Ambiguity: Due to differences in spelling, context, or culture, it might be difficult to distinguish between similar concepts.",
    "Additionally, it is quite challenging to distinguish between different entities.",
    "Usages:Low Resources Languages and Domain Specific are the two key difficulties encountered when using NER in Indian languages which is discussed further:(i) Low Resources Languages: Some Indian Languages have very limited digital content and resources, making it challenging to train and deploy NER models [45]."
  ]
}